---

<GuideLayout
  title="Bullet Force Killstreaks Guide – UAV, Nuke & All Streaks Explained"
  description="Complete Bullet Force killstreaks guide: all 6 streaks, exact kill requirements, PC activation keys (Arrow Keys), mobile controls, and UAV strategy tips."
  schema={schema}
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Guides', href: '/guides' }, { label: 'Killstreaks' }]}
  toc={toc}
>
  <h1>Bullet Force Killstreaks – Complete Guide (All 6 Streaks)</h1>

  <p>
    Killstreaks are rewards earned by getting consecutive kills without dying in Bullet Force. There are <strong>6 killstreaks</strong> ranging from the UAV (4 kills) to the devastating Nuke (25 kills). This guide covers every streak, exact kill requirements, how to activate them on PC and mobile, and how to use each one effectively.
  </p>

  <h2 id="what-are">What Are Killstreaks in Bullet Force?</h2>
  <p>
    Killstreaks (also called scorestreaks) are powerful abilities that activate once you earn a set number of kills in a row without dying. Each time you die, your kill counter resets. You must equip killstreaks in your <strong>loadout before a match starts</strong> — you cannot change them mid-game.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can equip up to <strong>3 killstreaks per loadout</strong>, filling slots 1, 2, and 3. In the PC browser version, each slot maps to a separate Arrow Key for activation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="list">All Bullet Force Killstreaks – Kill Requirements & Effects</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Killstreak</th>
        <th>Kills Required</th>
        <th>Duration</th>
        <th>Points</th>
        <th>Effect</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>UAV</strong></td>
        <td>4 kills</td>
        <td>30 seconds</td>
        <td>—</td>
        <td>Reveals all enemy positions on minimap. Countered by the Undetectable perk.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Counter-UAV</strong></td>
        <td>5 kills</td>
        <td>30 seconds</td>
        <td>—</td>
        <td>Disables the enemy team's minimap — they cannot see any players for 30 seconds.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Advanced UAV</strong></td>
        <td>8 kills</td>
        <td>30 seconds</td>
        <td>600 points</td>
        <td>Shows all enemies on minimap as directional triangles, revealing both position and facing direction. Countered by Undetectable.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Haste</strong></td>
        <td>9 kills</td>
        <td>25 seconds</td>
        <td>500 points</td>
        <td>Increases your sprint speed, aim speed, reload speed, and jump height for 25 seconds.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Super Soldier</strong></td>
        <td>13 kills</td>
        <td>30 seconds</td>
        <td>650 points</td>
        <td>Your bullets glow blue and deal significantly increased damage to enemies for 30 seconds.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Nuke</strong></td>
        <td>25 kills</td>
        <td>Instant</td>
        <td>4,000 points</td>
        <td>Drops a nuclear bomb that kills every player in the match — including you and your teammates.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <blockquote>
    <strong>Recommended beginner loadout:</strong> UAV (slot 1) + Counter-UAV (slot 2). Both are achievable in most matches and provide team-wide impact without requiring exceptional skill.
  </blockquote>

  <h2 id="activate-pc">How to Activate Killstreaks in Bullet Force on PC</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Equip killstreaks</strong> in your loadout before the match starts (Lobby → Edit Loadout → Killstreak slots).</li>
    <li><strong>Earn kills without dying</strong> — each kill charges your killstreak counter. Dying resets it to zero.</li>
    <li><strong>Watch for the ready indicator</strong> — when a killstreak is charged, its icon in the HUD lights up.</li>
    <li><strong>Press the activation key:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li><code>Left Arrow</code> — activate Killstreak Slot 1</li>
        <li><code>Up Arrow</code> — activate Killstreak Slot 2</li>
        <li><code>Right Arrow</code> — activate Killstreak Slot 3</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>UAV / Counter-UAV / Advanced UAV:</strong> activates instantly on key press.</li>
    <li><strong>Haste / Super Soldier:</strong> activates instantly and applies a buff to your character.</li>
    <li><strong>Nuke:</strong> activates a short countdown then kills everyone in the match.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="activate-mob">How to Activate Killstreaks in Bullet Force on Mobile</h2>
  <p>
    On Android and iOS, killstreak activation buttons appear on the right side of the HUD when a streak is ready. Tap the lit-up icon to deploy it immediately.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>UAV / Counter-UAV / Advanced UAV:</strong> tap the icon — activates instantly.</li>
    <li><strong>Haste / Super Soldier:</strong> tap the icon — buff applies to your character immediately.</li>
    <li><strong>Nuke:</strong> tap to trigger — a brief countdown plays before the explosion.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Mobile players have 6 loadout slots (vs 3 on PC), so you can pre-configure different killstreak setups per class and swap between them in the lobby.</p>

  <h2 id="uav">UAV Deep Dive – What Does UAV Mean in Bullet Force?</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>UAV stands for Unmanned Aerial Vehicle.</strong> In Bullet Force, deploying the UAV sends a drone above the map that scans for enemy locations. For 30 seconds, all enemy players appear as red dots on your entire team's minimap.
  </p>

  <h3>How many kills for UAV in Bullet Force?</h3>
  <p>The UAV requires <strong>4 consecutive kills without dying</strong>. It is the most accessible killstreak in the game and should be in every player's slot 1.</p>

  <h3>What counters the UAV in Bullet Force?</h3>
  <p>
    The <strong>Undetectable perk</strong> makes a player invisible to UAV and Advanced UAV scans. Players with Undetectable will not show as red dots on the minimap even when an enemy UAV is active.
  </p>
  <p>
    The <strong>Counter-UAV</strong> (5 kills) also directly counters enemy UAVs — it disables the opposing team's minimap entirely, neutralising any information from their active UAV.
  </p>

  <h3>What is the difference between UAV and Advanced UAV?</h3>
  <p>
    The regular UAV (4 kills) shows enemy locations as dots on the minimap. The <strong>Advanced UAV</strong> (8 kills) shows enemies as directional triangles — you see not only where they are, but also which way they are facing. This makes the Advanced UAV significantly more powerful for predicting flanks and pushes.
  </p>

  <h2 id="tips">Killstreak Strategy Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Always run UAV in slot 1</strong> — even beginner players can chain 4 kills. The intel it provides to your whole team is the highest value action at low kill counts.</li>
    <li><strong>Don't hold killstreaks</strong> — activate as soon as they are ready. Waiting for a "perfect moment" usually means dying first and losing the entire streak.</li>
    <li><strong>UAV + Counter-UAV combo</strong> — equip both. Use UAV to see enemies, and Counter-UAV to blind them. Your team fights with information, theirs fights blind.</li>
    <li><strong>Haste for aggressive rushes</strong> — the reload speed and sprint buff from Haste is best used immediately when pushing a flag or entering a building. Don't save it for defence.</li>
    <li><strong>Super Soldier on SMG builds</strong> — the damage buff pairs exceptionally well with high-RPM SMGs. At 13 kills you are already dominating — Super Soldier guarantees you continue to do so.</li>
    <li><strong>Nuke only in TDM</strong> — the Nuke's 4,000 points swing is most impactful in Team Deathmatch where scores are tight. In Conquest, objectives matter more than mass kills.</li>
    <li><strong>Equip Undetectable against UAV-heavy lobbies</strong> — if enemies consistently run UAV, Undetectable removes all the information they gain from it, protecting your flanking routes.</li>
  </ul>

